<h2>The short version</h2>
<p>
  We collect the minimum needed to sell and support our plugins: your email when you ask us for
  something, your order and licence details, and anonymous, cookieless analytics. We don&rsquo;t sell your
  data, we don&rsquo;t run advertising trackers, and you can have your data deleted any time by emailing
  <a href="mailto:support@revaudio.net">support@revaudio.net</a>. The rest of this is the detail.
</p>

<h2>1. Who we are</h2>
<p>
  RevAudio (&ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;us&rdquo;) builds and sells audio software plugins through this
  website, revaudio.net. We are the data controller for the personal data described here. For any privacy
  question or request, contact <a href="mailto:info@revaudio.net">info@revaudio.net</a> or
  <a href="mailto:support@revaudio.net">support@revaudio.net</a>.
</p>

<h2>2. What we collect</h2>
<p><strong>Information you give us.</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Your email address</strong>, when you join our list, sign up for the founding-tester beta, or
    contact us.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Beta-survey responses</strong>, if you choose to take part &mdash; your answers to the survey
    questions, submitted with your email.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Anything you send us by email</strong> (for example a support request), including the contents
    of that message.
  </li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Purchase information.</strong></p>
<p>
  Purchases are processed by <strong>Lemon Squeezy</strong>, our reseller and merchant of record. When you
  buy, you provide your name, email, and billing details <em>to Lemon Squeezy</em> &mdash; we never see or
  store your card number. Lemon Squeezy shares order details with us (such as your email, the product, and
  billing country) so we can deliver your download, issue your licence, and provide support. Lemon
  Squeezy&rsquo;s handling of your data is governed by its own privacy policy.
</p>
<p><strong>Licence information.</strong></p>
<p>
  To deliver and protect your purchase we generate a <strong>licence key</strong> tied to your email. When
  the plugin activates or periodically validates that key, limited technical data (such as your licence key
  and the fact of a validation request) is processed so we can confirm the licence is valid.
</p>
<p><strong>Information collected automatically.</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Cookieless analytics.</strong> We use Cloudflare Web Analytics to understand aggregate site
    traffic (such as page views, referrer, and country). It does <em>not</em> use cookies, does not
    fingerprint you, and does not track you across other sites.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Server and security logs.</strong> Our hosting and edge providers process standard technical
    data (such as IP address and browser type) to serve the site, keep it secure, and prevent abuse.
  </li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Cookies &amp; local storage</h2>
<p>
  We do not use advertising or cross-site tracking cookies. Your shopping cart is stored locally in your
  own browser (in <code>localStorage</code>) so it survives page navigation &mdash; that information stays
  on your device and is not sent to us until you check out. Our analytics is cookieless (see above).
</p>

<h2>4. Why we use your data (and our legal bases)</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>To deliver your purchase</strong> &mdash; download, licence key, and order support (to perform our contract with you).</li>
  <li><strong>To send you the emails you asked for</strong> &mdash; list updates or beta communications (with your consent, which you can withdraw at any time).</li>
  <li><strong>To improve the product</strong> &mdash; understanding beta-survey feedback and aggregate, cookieless traffic (our legitimate interest in improving our software and site).</li>
  <li><strong>To keep the service secure and lawful</strong> &mdash; preventing abuse and meeting tax and legal obligations (legitimate interest and legal obligation).</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Who we share it with</h2>
<p>
  We do <strong>not</strong> sell your personal data and we do not share it for anyone else&rsquo;s
  advertising. We use a small number of trusted service providers who process data on our behalf:
</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Lemon Squeezy</strong> (and its payment partners) &mdash; checkout, payments, tax, and order management, as merchant of record.</li>
  <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> &mdash; DNS and edge delivery, cookieless web analytics, and the workers that store beta-survey submissions and manage licences.</li>
  <li><strong>Vercel</strong> &mdash; hosting for this website.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  We may also disclose data if required by law, or to protect our rights, safety, or property.
</p>

<h2>6. International transfers</h2>
<p>
  We operate from Israel and our service providers may process data in other countries, including the
  United States. Where data is transferred internationally, we rely on the providers&rsquo; appropriate
  safeguards (such as standard contractual clauses or an applicable adequacy decision) to protect it.
</p>

<h2>7. How long we keep it</h2>
<p>
  We keep order and licence data for as long as your licence is active and as needed for support, tax, and
  legal record-keeping. We keep list and beta-signup emails until you unsubscribe or ask us to delete them.
  Beta-survey responses are kept for the duration of the beta programme and while we act on the feedback.
</p>

<h2>8. Your rights</h2>
<p>
  Depending on where you live, you have rights over your personal data &mdash; including the right to
  access it, correct it, delete it, restrict or object to its use, and receive a copy in a portable form.
  Where we rely on consent, you can withdraw it at any time. We do not sell personal data, and we do not
  discriminate against you for exercising your rights. To make a request, email
  <a href="mailto:support@revaudio.net">support@revaudio.net</a> &mdash; we&rsquo;ll respond within the time
  your law requires. If you&rsquo;re in the EU/EEA or UK and unhappy with our response, you may complain to
  your local data-protection authority.
</p>

<h2>9. Security</h2>
<p>
  We use reasonable technical and organisational measures to protect your data, and we work with providers
  who maintain their own security and PCI compliance. No method of transmission or storage is perfectly
  secure, but we take protecting your data seriously and act promptly if something goes wrong.
</p>

<h2>10. Children</h2>
<p>
  Our products and site are intended for adults and are not directed at children. We do not knowingly
  collect personal data from children. If you believe a child has provided us data, contact us and we will
  delete it.
</p>

<h2>11. Changes to this policy</h2>
<p>
  We may update this policy as our product line and the law evolve. Material changes will be dated at the
  top of this page.
</p>

<h2>12. Contact</h2>
<p>
  Privacy questions and requests: <a href="mailto:info@revaudio.net">info@revaudio.net</a><br />
  Support: <a href="mailto:support@revaudio.net">support@revaudio.net</a>
</p>
